window.docContents[135].resolve({"/Documentation-Features/#Zippers___-A-Documentation-Example--Documentation-Features--Anchors":{"contents":"An anchor is a named region of a module.\nAnchors can be included by name, rather than by line number.\nAn anchor is delimited by special comments:-- ANCHOR: anAnchor\ndef f : Nat → Nat := id\n#eval f 2\n-- ANCHOR_END: anAnchor\nThe comments themselves are removed, and there is no requirement that anchors be well-nested.\n\nAnchors can be specified using the (anchor := anAnchor) parameter to each module form.\nAdditionally, there are macro versions that take anchor names positionally, so for example```anchor anAnchor\n...\n```\nis equivalent to```module (anchor := anAnchor)\n...\n```\nand {anchorName anAnchor}`x` is equivalent to {moduleName (anchor := anAnchor)}`x`.\n\n","context":"Zippers: A Documentation Example\u0009Documentation Features","header":"2.2. Anchors","id":"/Documentation-Features/#Zippers___-A-Documentation-Example--Documentation-Features--Anchors"}});